###############################################################################
# AN — Pack Evidence Execution Fix (Slice 39)
#
# Slice 39 fixes Mode-B evidence execution that was non-functional in Slice 38.
# The stub ExecuteQueryAsync on IObservabilityConnector has been replaced by a
# dedicated IObservabilityQueryExecutor backed by AzureMonitorObservabilityQueryExecutor
# (LogsQueryClient + DefaultAzureCredential).
#
# PackEvidenceExecutor double-gate:
#   1. Pack deployment mode >= B
#   2. Configuration flag  Packs:EvidenceExecutionEnabled = true
#
# When both gates pass, KQL queries from pack evidence-collector files are
# executed against Azure Monitor via the new executor.  Results appear in
# TriageResponse.packEvidenceResults[] as PackEvidenceResultDto objects:
#   { packName, collectorId, connectorName, queryFile, queryContent,
#     resultJson, rowCount, errorMessage }
#
# NOTE: @workspaceId is synthetic — Azure Monitor cannot resolve it, so
# evidence queries will return errors.  This PROVES the real execution path
# runs (the old stub silently returned Success:false with no error detail).
###############################################################################

### AN1 — Mode-B triage: evidence execution path invoked
# Expected: 200 OK.  Response contains packEvidenceResults (may be [] or
#   items with errorMessage due to synthetic workspace).  The key proof is
#   that the execution path runs at all — Slice 38's stub never reached
#   Azure Monitor, so any error from Azure Monitor confirms the fix.
# @name triageEvidenceExecution
