###############################################################################
# AO — ModeB Evidence — Tenant Workspace Config (Slice 40)
#
# Slice 40 wires per-tenant workspace resolution into the ModeB evidence path.
# Instead of relying on a single global workspaceId in the request body, the
# executor now reads Tenants:<tenantId>:Observability:LogAnalyticsWorkspaceId
# from configuration and validates it against the SafeActions allowlist before
# executing KQL collectors.
#
# Resolution logic:
#   1. Tenant config lookup: Tenants:<tenantId>:Observability:LogAnalyticsWorkspaceId
#   2. Allowlist check: SafeActions:AllowedLogAnalyticsWorkspaceIds must include the GUID
#   3. Both gates must pass — failure produces per-item errorMessage, never a 4xx/5xx
#
# Scenario matrix:
#   AO1 — Configured tenant     → packEvidenceResults[] non-null, queries run
#   AO2 — Missing workspace     → per-item errorMessage = "missing_workspace"
#   AO3 — Not allowlisted       → per-item errorMessage = "workspace_not_allowlisted"
#   AO4 — Mode A tenant         → packEvidenceResults null (mode gate fires first)
###############################################################################

### AO1 — ModeB triage: tenant has workspace configured → evidence results present
# Expected: 200 OK.  packEvidenceResults[] is non-null and populated because
#   Tenants:tenant-slice40-configured:Observability:LogAnalyticsWorkspaceId is
#   set in config and the GUID is present in SafeActions:AllowedLogAnalyticsWorkspaceIds.
#   Individual items may carry errorMessage if Azure Monitor cannot resolve the
#   workspace in the local dev environment, but the resolution path itself runs.
# NOTE: Requires the server to be started with:
#   Tenants:tenant-slice40-configured:Observability:LogAnalyticsWorkspaceId = <valid-guid>
#   SafeActions:AllowedLogAnalyticsWorkspaceIds containing that same GUID
#   Packs:DeploymentMode = "B" and Packs:EvidenceExecutionEnabled = true
# @name triageModeB_TenantConfigured
