### ================================================================
### AU. Slice 104 — rollback/approve 400 on generic reason + telemetry
### ================================================================
###
### Dev Slice 104: ValidateAndNormalizeApprovalReason now applied to
###   rollback/approve. Low-signal reasons (ok, yes, lgtm, approved,
###   rejected, test, n/a) must return 400. Meaningful reasons → 200.
###   New telemetry counters: safeactions.proposal.recorded,
###   safeactions.rollback.recorded, safeactions.approval.recorded.
###
### Test cases:
###   AU1 — rollback/approve with generic reason "lgtm"      → 400
###   AU2 — rollback/approve with generic reason "ok"        → 400
###   AU3 — rollback/approve with empty reason               → 400
###   AU4 — approve with generic reason "yes"                → 400
###   AU5 — approve with generic reason "approved"           → 400
###   AU6 — approve with meaningful reason (non-existent ID) → 404
###
### NOTE: AU1–AU5 use ID 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099 (non-existent)
###       but 400 validation fires BEFORE DB lookup, so 400 is returned.

### AU1 · rollback/approve with "lgtm" (low-signal) → 400 Bad Request
###       Expected: 400, body = "Reason is too generic. Provide a specific approval rationale."
# @name rollbackApproveLgtm
POST {{baseUrl}}/safe-actions/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099/rollback/approve
x-tenant-id: tenant-slice-104
x-actor-id: dev-operator-104
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "lgtm"
}

