### ================================================================
### AT. Packs → SafeActions Record Creation  (Dev Slice 49)
### ================================================================
###
### Dev Slice 49: Mode C Only, STRICT — PackSafeActionRecorder bridges
###   pack safe-action proposals into real SafeAction proposal records
###   via ISafeActionProposalService.  Response includes a new field
###   packSafeActionRecordSummary (null when mode ≠ C or feature disabled).
###
### Test cases:
###   AT1 — ModeC triage: packSafeActionRecordSummary populated (happy path)
###   AT2 — ModeB triage: packSafeActionRecordSummary is null (mode gate)
###   AT3 — ModeC with feature disabled: packSafeActionRecordSummary is null
###   AT4 — ModeC triage: DTO shape verification for record items
###   AT5 — ModeA triage: packSafeActionRecordSummary is null (mode gate)
###############################################################################

### AT1 — ModeC triage: packSafeActionRecordSummary populated (happy path)
# Expected: 200 OK.  Response includes packSafeActionRecordSummary object with:
#   records[]       — per-proposal recording outcomes (PackSafeActionRecordItemDto[])
#   createdCount    — number of proposals successfully recorded (≥ 0)
#   skippedCount    — number of proposals skipped (not executable / governance denied)
#   failedCount     — number of proposals that failed recording
#   errors[]        — aggregate error messages (empty on full success)
#   Each record item has: packName, actionId, actionType,
#   actionRecordId (GUID or null), status ("Created"/"Skipped"/
#   "PolicyDenied"/"Failed"), errorMessage (null on success),
#   policyDenialReasonCode (null unless policy denied).
# NOTE: Server must be in Mode C (Packs:DeploymentMode = "C") with
#   Packs:SafeActionsEnabled = true.
# @name triageModeC_RecordSummaryHappyPath
POST {{baseUrl}}/agent/triage
Content-Type: application/json
x-tenant-id: {{tenantId}}

{
  "alertPayload": {
    "alertSource": "Azure Monitor",
    "fingerprint": "at1-modec-record-01",
    "title": "High CPU on prod-vm-01 — SafeActions record creation verification",
    "severity": "High",
    "firedAtUtc": "2025-07-29T10:00:00Z",
