### AU6 — ModeB triage: multiple proposals — each has independent validation
# Expected: 200 OK.  When the matched pack yields multiple safe-action
#   proposals, each item in packSafeActionProposals[] carries its OWN
#   validation result.  One proposal may be valid (definitionValidationErrorCode
#   = null, operatorPreview contains "Valid  : yes") while another may be
#   invalid (definitionValidationErrorCode = a non-null kebab-case code,
#   operatorPreview contains "Valid  : no — ...").
# This verifies per-item independence of the validator.
# NOTE: Server must be in Mode B (Packs:DeploymentMode = "B") with
